# RAVEZ OS — Cursor Rules

You are building RAVEZ OS, a nightclub management system (React + Vite + Tailwind).

## Architecture
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS + React Router
- Backend: PHP REST API at https://ravez-one.ru/backend/api.php (already exists, do NOT modify)
- Auth: JWT tokens stored in localStorage as `staff_token`
- API calls go through `src/api/client.js` — always use `api.get()` and `api.post()`

## Project structure
```
src/
  api/client.js          — API client (fetch wrapper)
  hooks/useAuth.js       — Auth context & hook
  components/            — Reusable UI components
    Layout.jsx           — Main layout (sidebar + content)
    Sidebar.jsx          — Navigation sidebar
    MobileNav.jsx        — Bottom nav for mobile
    ProtectedRoute.jsx   — Auth guard
  pages/                 — One file per page/module
    Login.jsx
    Dashboard.jsx
    Tasks.jsx
    Events.jsx
    Team.jsx
    ...
  utils/constants.js     — Roles, statuses, config
```

## Coding rules
- Language: Russian UI labels, English code (variable names, comments)
- Use functional components with hooks
- Use Tailwind classes, NO inline styles, NO CSS files per component
- Use lucide-react for icons
- Use recharts for charts
- Each page is a single file, max 200 lines. If bigger — extract components
- API calls: always handle loading and error states
- Mobile-first: design for 375px, scale up to desktop

## API conventions
- Base URL: configured in `src/api/client.js`
- Auth header: `X-Staff-Token: <token>`
- GET: `api.get('staff/list')` → calls `/backend/api.php?a=staff/list`
- POST: `api.post('task/save', { title, ... })` → POST with JSON body
- Response format: `{ ok: true, data: ... }` or `{ error: "message" }`

## Available API endpoints (main ones)
- `staff/login` POST { login, password } → { token, staff }
- `staff/me` GET → { staff: { id, name, role, ... } }
- `staff/list` GET → { staff: [...] }
- `tasks/list` GET → { tasks: [...] }
- `task/save` POST { title, description, status, assigned_to, deadline }
- `events/list` GET → { events: [...] }
- `event/save` POST { title, date, time_start, time_end, status }
- `shifts/list` GET → { shifts: [...] }
- `shift/save` POST { staff_id, date, time_start, time_end }
- `finances/list` GET → { finances: [...] }
- `finance/save` POST { type, amount, category, description, date }
- `guests/list` GET → { guests: [...] }
- `salary/list` GET → { salaries: [...] }
- `loyalty/tiers` GET → { tiers: [...] }
- `integrations/list` GET → { integrations: [...] }
- `analytics/dashboard` GET → { stats: { ... } }

## Design system
- Colors: brand-400 (#00e6c8) = primary accent, surface-50..900 = grays
- Font: DM Sans for body, Bebas Neue for display headings
- Border radius: rounded-lg (cards), rounded-md (buttons, inputs)
- Spacing: p-4/p-6 for cards, gap-4 for grids
- States: bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 (success), bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 (warning), bg-red-50 text-red-700 (danger)

## Roles (18 total, main ones)
owner, director, dev_director, admin, art_director, smm, designer,
stories_maker, light_tech, ambassador_manager, ambassador, promoter,
hostess, security, bartender, accountant, dj, hq

## When creating a new page
1. Create file in src/pages/
2. Add route in App.jsx
3. Add sidebar item in Sidebar.jsx
4. Follow the pattern from Dashboard.jsx
